Configuring the data flow task
  • Drag and drop a Script component and configure the variable as shown .

  • REMEMBER - To select the Script component as source option 



  • Click the edit script and add the c# script s shown .


Copy Paste the entire script below :

    public override void CreateNewOutputRows()

    {

        string filelocation = Variables.FILEPATH;

    

        string jsonFileContent = File.ReadAllText(filelocation);


        JavaScriptSerializer js = new JavaScriptSerializer() { MaxJsonLength = Int32.MaxValue };


        List<BuildingPermitsInMiami>productlistV = js.Deserialize<List<BuildingPermitsInMiami>>(jsonFileContent);


        foreach(BuildingPermitsInMiami rows in productlistV)

            {

            Output0Buffer.AddRow();

            Output0Buffer.CompanyCity = rows.CompanyCity;

            Output0Buffer.CompanyZip = rows.CompanyZip;

            Output0Buffer.CompanyName = rows.CompanyName;

            Output0Buffer.DeliveryAddress = rows.DeliveryAddress;

            Output0Buffer.FirstSubmissionDate = rows.FirstSubmissionDate;

            Output0Buffer.FolioNumber = rows.FolioNumber;

            Output0Buffer.IssuedDate = rows.IssuedDate;

            Output0Buffer.Latitude = rows.Latitude;

            Output0Buffer.Longitude = rows.Longitude;

            Output0Buffer.Miami21Zone = rows.Miami21Zone;

            Output0Buffer.NewAdditionCost = rows.NewAdditionCost;

            Output0Buffer.PermitNumber = rows.PermitNumber;

            Output0Buffer.PlanCreatedDate = rows.PlanCreatedDate;

            Output0Buffer.PlanAcceptedDate = rows.PlanAcceptedDate;

            Output0Buffer.ProcessNumber = rows.ProcessNumber;

            Output0Buffer.PropertyType = rows.PropertyType;

            Output0Buffer.RemodelingCost = rows.RemodelingCost;

            Output0Buffer.RemSQFT = rows.RemSQFT;

            Output0Buffer.RequiredCertificate = rows.RequiredCertificate;

            Output0Buffer.ScopeofWork = rows.ScopeofWork;

            Output0Buffer.Statusdate = rows.Statusdate;

            Output0Buffer.TotalCost = rows.TotalCost;

SCRIPT TASK C# QUERY (to convert first letter of every record to Uppercase and the rest to lowercase) :

  • Add another script component  as shown . This is added to convert the first letter of our columns to Capitals to make the output look presentable 
  • HERE REMEMBER to select the Script component as TRANSFORMATION while adding it 


c# query - copy and paste


 public override void Input0_ProcessInputRow(Input0Buffer Row)

    {

        /*

         * This is the only Code we have written. We created Function InitCapString that we used on

         * Input Column CountryName and Created New Column OutCountryName

         */


        Row.CompanyName1 = InitCapString(Row.CompanyName);

        Row.CompanyCity1 = InitCapString(Row.CompanyCity);

        Row.CompanyAddress1 = InitCapString(Row.CompanyAddress);

        Row.DeliveryAddress1 = InitCapString(Row.DeliveryAddress);

        Row.WorkItems1 = InitCapString(Row.WorkItems);

        Row.ScopeOfWork1 = InitCapString(Row.ScopeofWork);

    }


    private string InitCapString(string p)

    {

        return new

System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en").TextInfo.ToTitleCase(p.ToLower());

        throw new NotImplementedException();

    }
